# minion multi-source configuration
# ------------------------------------------------------------------
# Copy these lines into ~/.env (or export them in your shell) to enable
# multiple model sources. minion auto-loads ~/.env at startup.
#
# Each source needs at minimum a BASE_URL. API_KEY and MODEL are optional:
#   - API_KEY defaults to "sk-noop" (local servers ignore it)
#   - MODEL left blank → auto-resolved from the server's /v1/models
#
# API_KEY supports $indirection: $some_key means "look up the env var
# (or ~/.env key) named some_key". Useful when the key already lives
# somewhere and you don't want to duplicate it.

# Comma-separated list of source names. The first is the default at startup.
MINION_SOURCES=local,zai

# --- local: llama.cpp / vLLM on this machine ---------------------------
MINION_SOURCE_LOCAL_BASE_URL=http://localhost:8080/v1
MINION_SOURCE_LOCAL_API_KEY=sk-noop
# MODEL omitted → auto-resolved from server

# --- zai: Z.ai remote endpoint -----------------------------------------
MINION_SOURCE_ZAI_BASE_URL=https://api.z.ai/api/paas/v4
MINION_SOURCE_ZAI_API_KEY=***         # pulls "zai_test" from ~/.env
MINION_SOURCE_ZAI_MODEL=glm-x-preview

# --- together: built-in convenience source (Together AI) ---------------
# If TOGETHER_API_KEY is set (here or in your shell), minion auto-registers a
# `together` source at https://api.together.xyz/v1 defaulting to GLM-5.2.
# No MINION_SOURCE_TOGETHER_* vars needed — just:
TOGETHER_API_KEY=***

# Together hosts many models, so /source takes an optional model override:
#   /source together                    # → zai-org/GLM-5.2 (the default)
#   /source together zai-org/GLM-4.6    # → any other Together model id
# It's registered last, so it never displaces your default startup source.
# Defining MINION_SOURCE_TOGETHER_* below overrides the built-in entirely:
# MINION_SOURCE_TOGETHER_BASE_URL=https://api.together.xyz/v1
# MINION_SOURCE_TOGETHER_API_KEY=$TOGETHER_API_KEY
# MINION_SOURCE_TOGETHER_MODEL=zai-org/GLM-5.2

# Override the starting source (optional — defaults to the first in MINION_SOURCES)
# export MINION_ACTIVE=zai
